title: Razzle dazzle Jets new national champs
text:
Ipswich Jets claim State Championship with thrilling defeat of Newcastle Chris Garry The Courier-Mail Ipswich Jets claim State Championship with thrilling defeat of Newcastle Chris Garry The Courier-Mail Ipswich’s Marmin Barba streaks away for a crucial try in the State Championship. 
THE Ipswich Jets have been crowned national champions after winning a typically thrilling State Cup final against Newcastle. 
The Jets won 26-12 at ANZ Stadium with a powerhouse Rod Griffin try in the 70th minute sealing victory. 
The match was highlighted by a brilliant 90 metre Marmin Barba, younger brother of Ben, solo special, but soured with an ugly brawl in what was the curtain raiser to the NRL grand final. 
Ipswich were the dominant team in the first half as their unique brand of football confused the Knights. 
Sea Eagles-bound Jets hooker Matt Parcell scored first, in just the third minute, when he took off out of dummy half. Ipswich prop Rod Griffin was among his side’s best in downing Newcastle. 
The Jets did not change their idiosyncratic style, with their kick-offs short and producing turn overs as Knights players scrambled to field the ball. Other Stories
